name: Roman Rybkin
headline: Team Lead at Tutu@Hotels
creator: False
bio:
I am a developer and team leader with over 8 years of experience. Starting my career as a Linux developer using C and C++, I transitioned to backend development in Golang. I have participated in research projects, worked with OS kernels, and developed backends for B2C and B2B products. Half of my career has been spent working as a developer in taxi companies. Currently, I am a team leader of a fullstack team. 
I am constantly learning new things, enjoy building innovative products, creating successful teams, and improving organizational processes. My goal is to develop both my technical and managerial skills.

headline: AI Robotics Engineer || Data Scientist
creator: False
bio:
Passionate about using the power of data to drive decision making and process improvements, I bring two years of professional experience as a Data Scientist, specializing in Computer Vision and Machine Learning framework development. I have successfully implemented and optimized numerous semantic segmentation projects, making significant contributions to the analysis of satellite imagery. In my career, I have not only focused on achieving technical advancements, but also on sharing knowledge, as demonstrated by my role in leading a mentorship program for budding data scientists.

I am skilled in developing end-to-end ML pipelines, deploying models in production environments, and managing dynamic teams. My commitment to continuous learning and improvement, coupled with my ability to translate complex data into actionable insights, enables me to tackle challenging problems and deliver high-quality solutions.

Feel free to connect with me or send a message if you're interested in collaborations, or simply want to chat about the latest trends in machine learning and computer vision!

name: Harrif Saliu
headline: Software Engineer | Flutter Developer at 3Line Limited
creator: False
bio:
Hello!

I am a Software Engineer with about 7 years of  experience in mobile and web application development. I thrive on creating scalable, user-focused solutions that align with business goals. My journey has taken me from crafting complex back-end systems to building mobile apps that are intuitive, reliable, and impactful.

Currently, as a Flutter Developer at 3Line Limited, I have led the development of multiple high-impact applications, including agency banking and merchant monitoring solutions. One of my proudest accomplishments is developing an app that surpassed 10,000 downloads across the Google Play Store and iOS App Store‚Äîa testament to the usability and reliability of the solutions I create.

My work often involves collaborating with cross-functional teams to define app features, enhance user experiences, and deploy seamless applications to app stores. By leveraging MVC and MVVM architectural patterns, I ensure that my codebase is maintainable, scalable, and adheres to SOLID principles. Whether it's debugging existing applications, conducting stakeholder meetings, or integrating REST APIs, I bring a problem-solving mindset and a commitment to excellence to every project.

What sets me apart is my ability to bridge the technical and user-centric aspects of development. I believe in building applications that not only meet functional requirements but also delight users with intuitive design and smooth performance. My goal is to contribute meaningful solutions that empower users and help organizations achieve their goals.

My extensive experience lies in working at the intersection of strategy, digital transformation, operations optimisation, and innovation to develop and execute complex and sustainable growth programs. 

I am passionate about disruptive innovation and sustainability technologies in the retail, telecommunications, and consumer goods industries and have conducted leading research in these areas. I have also co-authored Bain's "Management Outlook 2023" and contributed to the "Organising ESG for Retail Companies" section, which provides a comprehensive case study of leading retail and FMCG companies and their best practices for implementing ESG strategies into daily business operations.

My goal is to actively contribute to advancements in both research and industry domains, leveraging my expertise to drive innovation in robotics and automation.

Eager to cultivate my communication and interpersonal skills through meaningful interactions with industry professionals, I am actively seeking a challenging opportunity where I can gain hands-on experience and make significant contributions to the community. With a relentless focus on teamwork and collaboration, I am dedicated to fostering positive change and contributing my skills and expertise towards impactful solutions in both academic and industrial spheres.

bio:
Cybersecurity enthusiast, open-source contributor. 
Currently focusing on web and mobile application security.
Have an experience building S-SDLC in both isolated on-premise and cloud environments; working with methodologies such as OTG (OWASP) and STRIDE (MS); applying following security standards in practice: fintech (PCI DSS, GOST 57580), security frameworks (ISO27001, SOC2), personal data privacy aspects (GDPR, 152 FZ).  
Had CTF participation as both player and organizer. 
My academic achievements includes bachelor and master degree in Information security as well as published papers on security topics.

name: Boris Makaev
headline: Python Software Developer - VIDATOR DIGITAL DMCC
creator: False
bio: Hello everyone! I am Software Developer. Currently I am studying Computer Science at the Vienna University and I've decided to search for open job positions. For an extensive period I was working as Python backend developer in the field of Video Hosting. Also, I have an extensive experience in Java backend development. I love technical and optimization problems that concern application performance. Through out the years I was interested in many areas of Computer Science and Software Engineering, especially during my University days where I've tried myself in Computer Vision, Machine Learning, DevOps and FrontEnd. It was interesting and handy experience that gave me extra knowledge that helped me along the way. That "Jack-of-all-trades"-ish approach (or you could say Breadth-first oriented approach to life) gave me an opportunity to work closely with all of my teammates no matter which part of the project they were working on, find and solve problems in any layer of application fast. Also it allows me to quickly learn a new topic, technology for using in my work. But of course no matter how much I like to spread my attention across different fields of software engineering I prioritise backend development above all others.
